theorem Topology.closureInterior_union_eq {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A B : Set X} :
    closure (interior (A ∪ B)) =
      closure (interior A) ∪ closure (interior B) := by
  calc
    closure (interior (A ∪ B))
        = closure (interior A ∪ interior B) := by
          simpa [interior_union]
    _   = closure (interior A) ∪ closure (interior B) := by
          simpa [closure_union]

theorem Topology.interiorClosureInterior_eq_self_of_P2_closed
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hA : IsClosed A) (hP2 : Topology.P2 A) :
    interior (closure (interior A)) = A := by
  -- We prove the two inclusions separately.
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  · -- `⊆` : `interior (closure (interior A)) ⊆ A`
    -- Since `A` is closed, `closure (interior A) ⊆ A`.
    have hSub : closure (interior A) ⊆ A := by
      have : closure (interior A) ⊆ closure A :=
        closure_mono (interior_subset : interior A ⊆ A)
      simpa [hA.closure_eq] using this
    -- Monotonicity of `interior` gives the desired inclusion.
    exact interior_mono hSub
  · -- `⊇` : `A ⊆ interior (closure (interior A))`
    exact hP2
